Name: adult mesoblastic nephroma
Definition: A mixed neoplasm that is seen mostly in early infancy and that consists of classic and cellular (atypical) variants.
Synonym: mixed epithelial and stromal tumour of kidney

Name: mixed germ cell-sex cord neoplasm
Definition: A cell type cancer that has_material_basis_in abnormally proliferating cells derives_from germ cells.

Name: carcinosarcoma
Definition: A mixed cell type cancer that has_material_basis_in carcinomatous (epithelial tissue) and sarcomatous (connective tissue) components.

Name: obsolete malignant soft tissue neoplasm of central nervous system
Definition: A mixed cell type cancer that has_material_basis_in carcinomatous (epithelial tissue) and sarcomatous (connective tissue) components.

Name: mixed epithelial stromal tumour
Definition: A viral infectious disease that results_in infection in cats
